Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language processing tasks and information retrieval, which are both subfields of computer science. The focus of the paper is on word embeddings and named entities, which are central components of natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses approaches to training embeddings, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions performance evaluation, which is a common topic in the sub-categories cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of co-occurrence graphs, which is a topic in the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
